  <p>
    <strong>n8n vs Zapier</strong> is the default comparison for workflow automation. Zapier (-10% trend)
    remains familiar; n8n climbs on AI, self-host, and cost control.
  </p>

  <h2>At a glance</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pricing model</strong> — Zapier: per-task SaaS. n8n: self-host infra + optional Cloud tiers.</li>
    <li><strong>Hosting</strong> — Zapier: cloud only. n8n: cloud or self-host.</li>
    <li><strong>Complexity</strong> — Zapier: shallow learning curve. n8n: steeper, far more flexible.</li>
    <li><strong>AI agents</strong> — n8n: native AI nodes + MCP patterns. Zapier: AI features on select plans.</li>
    <li><strong>Code</strong> — n8n: JavaScript/Python in nodes. Zapier: limited code steps.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Choose Zapier if</h2>
  <p>You need the fastest non-technical setup and budget is not execution-heavy.</p>

  <h2>Choose n8n if</h2>
  <p>You run agencies, AI pipelines, or high-volume sync — especially with our <a href="/free-n8n-workflows">free templates</a>.</p>

